reviews:
Good value for he money. Everything is newly renovated, fresh and clean. Good service.
Second time I was here. This time the bathroom was larger. If you are XL size you might want to make sure that you get one of the rooms with larger bathroom.
Hotel LÃ©opold will be my home away in Paris. It's comfortable, calm, close to public transportation, several nice restaurants and Jardin du Luxembourg.

Welcome to the best of the hospitality business: the French welcome is in this boutique hotel .
From my arrival to my departure the entire staff was very nice (they all speak english) . Room are clean and we donât hear any noise from inside . You will understand the place when you will see the menu of the breakfast
. We will definitely come back. Merci

Great little boutique hotel in Paris. Rooms are small, but expected. Service was good and prompt. Really small elevator and water temperature changes during a shower. Other than that, good hotel. Close to lots of restaurants and within 10 mins of Luxembourg gardens.

Good location, close to the metro station which leads to main city attractions. Good breakfast, it was having all you need to start a day with some energy> The rooms were cosy and pretty designed. I would definately recommend

The hotel was situated close to the metro which was very useful for us to move around city> The rooms were cosy and nicely decorated> Staff was very helpfull and welcoming. I loved the cake that is every morning on the counter of reception. Definately will be back!

we stayed for a couple of days in Paris, this hotel is very cute and a real boutique hotel. rooms are a the small size but well decorated. beds and pillows are so confortable !
staff is amazing too, very nice with good restaurants advice.

Gorgeous boutique hotel in a great location. The staff are super friendly and helpful. There is room service provided by a local restaurant and in-house breakfast is available. The coffee is brewed not espresso and breakfast is quite expensive so if you can get it in your room rate I recommend, otherwise there are some great Boulangerie within easy access (with the best croissants I've ever had!). The stairs in the hotel are steep, there is a lift that stops mid-floor so you will need to carry your bags up a half dozen stairs. This was not a problem for us but would be difficult if you have accessibility needs. Loved the late checkout, comfy beds, quality toiletries and fluffy towels. It's close to the metro, and a 15 euro taxi to Champs Elysees. I would definitely stay again.

The hotel is wonderfully situated between 2 metro stops for easy access to the heart of Paris and is in the middle of a characterful and historic area perfect for eating and drinking. The hotel itself is charming, some light find the rooms a little small but this is Paris and it is fantastic value. What really makes the hotel special though is the staff who are universally friendly and genuinely want you to have the best stay. And the excellent breakfast is available to noon!

I visited for 4 nights and it was a great experience. The staff was really friendly and welcoming when we entered the hotel. We dropped our bags and went to the Luxembourg park which is like a 5 min walk. Which is amazing. There is also a metro station at every corner of the street.

The hotelroom was super clean and nice. The bed was very comfortable and the shower was amazing. No need to bring your body wash and bodylotion. The hotel has itâs own line of products which smell amazing and you can even purchase them if you would like to. The rooms where really quite so that was really nice as well.

You can ask for a bottle of water which is free of charge which we asked for a lot because the tap water is not really drinkable. You also get a kettle and coffeemachine with your room.

At the other side of the road is a amazing restaurant called Masion Edgar. Really worth a visit. For lunch or diner!

Overall really loved this hotel. Would highly recommend.

Really nice boutique Hotel. Super Friendly staff. Small room but we know that when booking. Very clean though. And the breakfast was really nice. We absolutely recommend :)

Also very nice personal touches such as handwritten note and bottle of wine.

We stayed at this lovely hotel for a long weekend.
The hotel staff were delightful and could not do enough. The breakfasts & reception exquisite.
Our bedroom & bathroom were perfect.
We come again for sure.

Nice staff, very helpful ladies from reception (thanks for them I found so many nice places in Paris), who always greet you with a smile. Clean, cosy and in reasonable price. Very nice breakfast as well. Satisfaction guaranteed!

Beautiful and cosy place in heart of Montparnasse, close to all tourist atractions. Tasty breakfast and amazingly helpful staff, they pay attention to lot of nice details like chocolate in the room and welcome postcard. I will definately be back

We stayed in a junior suite for three nights as a family of four. The hotel has great character, very friendly and helpful staff (welcome cake on arrival!) and is well located for local restaurants and exploring the city, either on foot or via the metro.

The continental breakfast was simple but delicious and set us up for the day.

Weâd definitely stay again.

My stay was very pleasant and perfect at Leopold hotel.
Well located in Paris in a touristic area, staff was hekpfull and nice to us.
I recommend this hotel and will be back when visiting paris again.

An unforgettable stay in the best holteu in France. Very nice facility, delicious breakfasts at a high level, very helpful and friendly staff in a great location. I recommend it, we will definitely be back!

Great boutique hotel perfectly located in Paris. The personnel was extremely attentive and the room sizes are typical of a Parisian hotel (for foreigners please note they are on a smaller size)
Very charming - and great morning breakfast.
Will come back!

We chose the hotel as we wanted to stay in Montparnasse for a particular event but also wanted to be able to get around the city easily. Close to metro and mainline train station. We walked from the left bank a couple of times. Hotel was quiet throughout our stay even though our room faced the main busy street. Comfortable clean room, cool decor. Cute bathroom. Partner was delighted with huge bed after I'd warned him it might be a double. Staff were helpful but we didn't have much reason for interaction as we had everything we needed. Very enjoyable stay.

The bed was like sleeping on clouds. I loved the chocolate. The bathroom was bigger than most hotels I stayed in. The area was perfect lots of cafes to eat at. It was close to the metro. The elevator and stairs were scary! I had trouble opening two doors to get to my room.

Lovely hotel, well situated for restaurants and close to Raspail Metro. Rooms typically small as often in Paris boutique style hotels. Friendly staff. Breakfast ok but low on fresh fruit. Generally though very good.
24 hr reception a plus for an hotel of this type.

we had a lovely stay at this property, team is lovely and very warm with our fur pet.
they kindly had a cushion, bowls and a treat in our room.
it was easy to go to all main monuments and the neighborhood was still quiet and charming.

all the staff was welcoming and super nice ! we had a personalized welcome in our room and we felt super at ease. it was easy to go everywhere in Paris thanks to the subway stations nearby. bakeries at the breakfast are to die for.

Amazing crew, well located hotel, breakfast absolutely stunning.
Exactly what I hope to find in a city hotel.
The whole team was amazingly helpful with any ask or question.
You have really smooth access to various public transport options.

This was my 2nd time at Leopold for a 4 night stay back in May 2022 (sorry for the late review, but better late than never) and it continues to be my favourite place to stay when I come back home to Paris. Once again, I was treated wonderfully by the staff at checkin and throughout my stay.

Was given a nice room on top floor facing the street, and it was very quiet (Iâm very sensitive to noise). Room was perfect. Donât expect large rooms, but still perfectly adequate for me travelling solo, and easily for couples as well. Bathroom a little cramped, (especially since the towels are so large and fluffy, you need room!). It was very hot back at the time and the AC worked like a charm.

Only inconvenience was that the wifi was very weak in my room. When I was by the door, it worked fine, but on the bed, I barely got any signal. I mentioned this at checkout and they were already aware and were in the process of having it corrected. (Not an issue during previous stay, so it it must have been specific to that room or floor)

Donât skip the breakfast. It is amazing and they take pride in only offering quality ingredients (mainly locally sourced/circuit court). The is a welcome change from so many hotels that donât care since they think foreigners wonât know the difference. Staff was telling me that they are making it even better. Canât wait to see the improvements.

Just a small suggestion, please offer some French newspapers. Otherwise, itâs a great place to stay. Truly a hidden gem in Montparnasse. At checkout, I already made a booking for my next stay (Sept 30) and looking forward to it.

Michel R

The hotel is lovely, and the location is terrific - a 2 minute walk to the Metro. Rooms are nicely furnished and the rain head shower is wonderful. Staff were friendly, and breakfast was excellent. The Hotel is walking distance to plenty of restaurants, shopping, and sight seeing. I would happily stay here again.

We chose Hotel Leopold as arriving in Paris at Gare due Nord and leaving from Gare du Montparnasse. Excellent location - 2 mins walk from Metro on Line 4

Lovely area with good restaurants - plus Montparnasse Tower and Luxembourg Gardens nearby and maker to visit

Excellent communications before during and after stay, warm welcome, great room - small but had everything you could want in it and in the right place.- bathroom the same. Super breakfast Lovely toiletries. Design detail was fantastic especially the lighting.

We enjoyed our stay!

rooms were perfect size (some people on here said theyâre too small - for 2 people itâs fine!) showers are a bit small but didnât affect the stay at all! view is amazing, location is too - metro not even a minute walk away super easy to get around paris! reception staff were lovely and room was also cleaned every day (you have the option of do not disturb though!) super lovely decoration around the hotel and i personally felt very safe in the area, lots of restaurants not far away at all (iâd recommend broadway caffe at the end of the road if you like italian! amazing pizza) overall amazing stay - nothing bad to say at all!

This hotel is beautiful and very well decorated, room is also beautiful, and bed very comfortable.
Cocktails at the bar are unique and good. All the staff are welcoming and nice and gave us very good advise for restaurants and musÃ©um tours

Cozy rooms. Privacy was amazing. Clean rooms. Friendly staff. This hotel was very close to restaurants and transportation in a very nice part of Paris. I loved how the rooms felt very private and relaxing from a huge day out in the city. I loved how I could have my amazing Nexpresso coffee in the morning in my room with no-one bugging me. They provided me with a coffee machine upon my request. I am not a morning person so having coffee in the room was great.

We had to have an emergency stop over in Paris after car problems and booked into The Hotel Leopold at the last minute with our 2 grandchildren who were travelling with us. From the very first moment, nothing was too much trouble and we were made to feel oh so welcome! Although not big, the rooms are perfectly clean and very comfortable. A quiet drink in the bar before heading out to eat, and we were set for a lovely evening in a great area with so much choice within a five minute walk. The metro is 500 yards from the hotel so some of our party,(!) headed in to see the Eiffel Tower which was a 15 minute ride. Breakfast was plentiful and varied and again, everything was sparkling clean and as you would expect in France, the coffee perfect! Thank you Achour and Elena for looking after us, printing out my tickets and generally being so lovely! ð

Had a great stay here with such helpful front desk service, especially the receptionist Marine!!! She lived in the US, so her English is fantastic and she helped with ALL my big and small questions!!! The location is accessible to everywhere you would want to visit in Paris! Highly Recommend this friendly hotel. Please tell Marine, hello!!

My husband stayed for 5 days and loved it. Friendly staff, excellent service, clean and cute room with a nice street view, loved the breakfast , decor, great location, close to cafes , metro, very safe area. I will definitely come back and recommend to friends.

Great stay at Hotel Leopold. We had a Family Room with two adjoining rooms and it worked great for our family of five. The staff was exceptionally accommodating - we had a snag with our booking due to our bankâs travel agency and they worked expeditiously to resolve it (even cane up with alternative solutions despite it not being their issue). The staff was super friendly to our kids, very helpful with anything we needed , etc. By far one of the best customer service experiences we have ever had.

Outside of the staff, the rooms are well decorated and appointed. They are typical size for what you expect in Paris. The beds are comfortable, ample AC, and there is a good breakfast option with the stay.

I did see someone else mention that the metro was far away, and clearly they are confused (unless Paris is actively digging new metro stations). The hotel is very close to the Raspail stop on 6 - getting anywhere from the hotel is a breeze.

We had a good stay overall and we would certainly stay here again!

A real nugget in the center of paris !
close to the main monuments notre dame, eiffel tower, luxembourg garden, well decorated and pleasant room,
generous breakfast with quality artisanal products.
The staff are lovely and full of good advice!

Pleasant staff. Small rooms (usual Paris) and tiny bathrooms (even for Paris). Booked for a transition night because it was close to Montparnasse but discovered it was a half mile walk from the station. Tiny elevator and all rooms require half/floor of steps. Great access to Metro (not relevant for us here) and interesting neighborhood. Three stars for us but might be more for others.

We stayed in room #201 for 2 nights in may 2022. Room was 11m2. You could hardly move around the bed without hiting the wall stool or table. Bathroom is minute, shower even worse. Because of the room size, in bed, you have the aircon that blows in your face all night and you had to keep it on as if not the room was hot.
Noisy, you are next to the starircase and hear everything.
We came down for breakfast. 3/4 of the small sitting area had not been cleaned up and the rest was taken.
Definately not worth your money. We paid 327â¬ per night!

It is a very nice hotel, well restored, with a trendy and neat decoration.
Cozy and quiet room. Little touches in the room to make you feel welcome and expected.
Extra caring staff throughout the stay.
A great experience!

My family and I came for a 5 days visit to Paris and Normandy. we had two rooms near each other. the hotel is beautiful and well located. the employees are lovely. We can only recommend this incredible hotel!

This was our first time in Paris and I'm glad we choose this hotel. Even before we arrived, the contact was nice and helpful. We arrived before noon and could get our room at once. We had a very good breakfast served on our room without extra charge. The interieur of the room is very nice, everything is chosen with love an fits perfectly, the big bed was very comfortable. The bathroom is tiny, but everything worked well. Free showergel, shampoo and bodylotion. Staff is very friendy and helpful with recommendations, e.g. booking restaurants.
The hotel is located 2 minutes from the MÃ©tro station Raspail, line 4. You can reach all interesting places in short time.
I'm sure my next trip to Paris will lead me to the "Hotel Leopold."

This hotel is lovely even before you arrive. They send a pre check in email which is considerate, charming and helpful. We got early checkin which was a lovely addition and is hard to find in Paris. When we arrived the staff greeted us with a small, a complimentary bottle of wine (because we booked through Secret Escapes) and gave us all the information we needed, plus our menu so that we could order breakfast in bed (!). The room was tastefully painted and designed, the mini bar had some snacks and juice in which you could help yourself too, there were dressing gowns and slippers, and the bed with its white, crisp sheets was very comfy. We didn't miss anything. The bathroom was on the smaller side, but perfectly functional and well stocked. A handwritten note and some toffees were in the room, which was a nice touch. The windows were thick but of course you could hear some traffic, but it wasn't disturbing. They gave good recommendations and it seemed nothing was too much trouble. I would highly recommend and would stay again!

we had a three nights stay in this parisian cocoon ! staff was very welcoming, hotel was charming, bedding was so confortable !
we were lucky enough to have sun every day and we enjoyed the terrasse with their cocktails, it was such a happy moment !

Spend three days here with the family. Ample suite room. Easy accessible (public car Parc and metro at walking distance). Coffee machine , water boiler and fridge in the room. Clean rooms, usb chargers standard. Friendly staff, full breakfast.

Our room was delightful on the top floor and very clean.
Team was super welcoming and gave us very good tips to enjoy the city,
they kept our luggage on our last day so we can visit fondation Cartier nearby,
We will come back for sure !

Loved my 5 day stay here! The service was incredible, every staff member went out of their way to make my stay better. Location is so great! So many nice cafes and restaurants close by. Loved my cute room, beautiful view of the Fall trees outside the window. Completely recommend!

Very nice stay and wonderful team. breakfast was awesome.
The team was so nice and helpful, they helped us organize our restaurants reservations and recommended hot spot in the city. We will definitly come back to visit them next time we are in Paris !

Although the room was small, everything was in the right place. It felt clean, fresh and very cozy. The bed was perfect and the breakfast was one of the best features of the hotel.
I had an unforgettable vacation and would return to this hotel.

I stayed at the Hotel Leopold for 3 nights during my stay in Paris in early September 2022.

When I arrived (following my red-eye flight from Canada), I was surprised to see that my room was available in the morning. I had booked a Superior room and asked for a shower and overlooking the back. These were both fulfilled however when I entered the room, a couple minor issues we found in the room (which could have been addressed during my stay), however the very friendly receptionist offered to move me to another room instead. I was offered a bigger room as no other rooms seemed to be available.

The room was spacious and very clean (important these days). The hotel itself is very quiet and I didn't hear any noise from adjacent rooms or from outside. The weather was quite warm for the season (31c) and the AC worked like a charm and was super quiet.

Bathroom was spacious however the shower itself was a bit on the small size, but not a big issue. The soaps of good quality with a great scent.

I took the breakfast option when I reserved (highly recommended) and it was just as great as everyone says. I'm from France originally and I know good bread and vienoiseries. They get theirs from the bakery next door which has won awards for having the best baguette a few years ago. The breakfast is Ã  la carte (rather than buffet) but you can choose whatever you want such as baguette or slice bread, croissants, pains au chocolat, fresh fruit, yogourt, fresh juices, cheese, etc.. You select what you want at check-in and are of course free to change or add more if want to more of something. The lady serving the breakfast was super nice as well.

Location is amazing. If coming from CDG, you can take the RER line B direct to Port Royal station and then about a 5-10 min walk to the hotel through the side street. Way cheaper than a CAB (10.30 Euros) and faster as well! It is also conveniently located next to several subway station including Vavin right next door. There are also many buses going to or through Montparnasse. The neighborhood is one of the best in Paris since it's not too touristy yet still very lively with many known restaurants shops and theatres. Highly recommend "La Coupole" if you want to experience the real brasserie.

Anyhow, I had a superb stay and hope to stay here again on my next stay!

Very nice Little Hotel with very friendly staff. It is located central in Paris montparnasse. The breakfast ist pretty good and fresh. We had a pretty nice stay there. We will come back there for sure.

Location: This nice âpetitâ hotel sits right in between Raspail en Vavin metro stations. Which makes it very easy to travel to and from! It is within walking distance from Jardin Luxembourg.

Room: Small but perfect. Smart design features, enough power sockets and even USB chargers. Integration of closet space and night stand helps to make the room conveniently compact! Bathroom is small bit clean and nicely done! Soft big towels and fresh amenities with a nice scent!

Breakfast: BOOK IT! the bread is amazing. Croissants are fantastic and the Pain au Chocolate is heaven! Even under COVID restrictions they do their very best to make it a nice experience!

Staff: Very very friendly! They do their best to make your stay the most enjoyable. Breakfast lady was very sweet and both of the night staff that I met were attentive and looking after my needs.

Tips: My room had a door in front sharing a mini hall way with one other room. I guess this is how you create a family room. My tip would be to put a small hook on the first door so it can stay open if itâs not used as a family room. This gives a bit more space to the guests and also limits the noise of door slamming when going in and out of your room. The room was completely soundproof the only thing I could hear was this door.

5 out of 5 stars, would love to stay here again! Recommend booking solo as well as couples!

We stayed there just one night because, due to our travel plans, we were looking for a place close to Montparnasse train station. The staff was super friendly and welcoming. In fact, the hotel was almost full, so we got an upgrade to a superior room. Still, the superior room was rather small, but still cozy, clean, and nicely decorated. Full equipped bathroom, nice and comfortable bed. Decent prices, although we did not book it with breakfast.

Great hotel with lovely styled rooms. The staff was friendly and speaks perfectly English. The location of the hotel is great to explore the city. I would recommend staying here for a nice weekend get-away.

Its for sure a hotel that we would stay in again. It is very charming, with a good structure and its very comfortable for those on vacation as a couple. It is also very close to the metro station in a very good and quiet region. The people who work there are very kind.

We were with a family of four and had two seperate rooms (one at the front and one at the back). The rooms were very small but very clean and the beds were big and comfortable. The breakfast was good, with delicious croissants. The reception staff was friendly and took time for every customer. Also the area Montparnasse is cozy with plenty of cafes and restaurants. The metro stop Raspail was very close.

I stayed here for three nights and the receptionist was very patient. The room is relatively clean and tidy. The breakfast is also pretty good. The room is slightly smaller. Overall it was a very good experience.

We felt really welcome in Hotel Leopold, and enjoyed the attention to our needs, responsiveness and loved the overall experience. Air conditioning was welcome during a hot spell in August. As a cherry on the cake they had a good deal with the nearby underground parking facility and you pay the parking at the hotel.

The hotel was very good, the location was ideal for our trip as the subway was only 100 meters away. The rooms are small, but well used. Everything was as advertised. The value was very good, the breakfast included extremely good. The best part was the very friendly staff.

Cleanliness absolutealy needs to be improved- room was dusty and there were stains in the bathroom. Eben with the sign "please make up my room" the room was not cleaned once during the weekly stay.
Otherwise the room was ok, nice bathroom and bed, quiet, unfortunately closet cant open fully.

Loved my stay, friendly and helpful staff (they also spoke English) the bed was comfy and there was plenty of room for storage. My room had a window which you could open to have a street view which was a nice plus! Many food establishments around, and close to the metro. Would absolutely come back

Great value. Rooms rather small, but rest is great. Very friendly and helpful staff. Very clean and well maintained. Perfect for a long weekend in Paris. We were there with two kids (9yo) who loved it as well (even though it is not a "kids" hotel) and two adults.

We would like to recommand hotel Leopold for itâs location, ( 1 minute from Metro), the clean and nice decorated rooms, the aminities in the bathroom were also lovely. Breakfast is TOP ( super granola) and due to Covid breakfast was also served in our room. From the first minute at our check-in ( fresh glass of water was offered) to the last minute of our check-out Melanie did everything she could to make our stay perfect! Thanks a lot! We will come back and recommend the hotel. ( we also had a perfect lunch at Maison Edgar !)

This little quaint hotel is perfectly located if you like walking through Paris. Les Jardins du Luxembourg are a 15-minute walk. The little streets around Montparnasse are filled with bars and restaurants,
The hotel rooms are small but very clean. We found the beds a little hard.
Staff are very friendly.

I had a really wonderful stay at this very parisian stylish hotel. Every single detail was perfect. The room - at the 7th floor - had a beautiful view, no noise at all, super cleaned and comfortable. All members of the staff were extremely kind, professional and ready to help. The 14th arrondissement is my fav in Paris. Walk from the hotel to the Jardin du Luxembourg (10 min) and you'll se what I mean. I'll definitely be back to the Leopold.

- Dinner is not worth the price and does not correspond to that of a 4-stars hotel.
- Breakfast is minimalist (croissants & cafÃ©) and does not correspond to that of a 4-stars hotel.
-Staff in front desk were mean and sassy. Not helpful or gentle.

Conveniently placed close to Montparnasse's railway station, this comfortable "typical" hotel is made pleasant by the quality of its staff and of its room service.
My standard bedroom was small but comfortable and silent.

Beautiful boutique Hotel, a nice walk distant from Parisâ center.
Good quality of food, also for room service...
I will come back for sure in the next future...
Room are small but well organized and nothing is missing

+ Good location & Service.
- Dinner is not worth the price and does not correspond to that of a 4-stars hotel.
- Breakfast is minimalist (croissants & cafÃ©) and does not correspond to that of a 4-stars hotel.

Perfectly located - a few minutes from the Jardin du Luxembourg and 1min from the metro station. We loved the floral rooms - pretty, very comfortable and super clean ! Friendly and very available staff. Also, the arrangements related to Covid-19 pleased us a lot, in particular the breakfast served in the room!

Perfect hotel that couldn't have been more accommodating. Marie and the team were so professional and lovely, beautiful room and perfect service. Printed out everything I asked for, brought me up coffee capsules, always hot water, fresh towels, cleaned room everyday, called me as my alarm etc.. Will be coming back! :)

The hotel is very well located, close to the main metro lines and also very central.
The staff is friendly and the room was very clean, the products are high quality.
Although the lamps were not working and the light was too dark in the room for me to read my work papers.

Nice location and lovely staff alsways ready to make you feel like home by advicw and offering solution to every question. Raspail is in a walking distance from montparnase and many bars restaurants were nearby

Like a diamond - small but perfect - was our room. Just enough room to walk around the bed! Loved the decor & very clean. We were supposed to receive complimentary champagne & chocolates but, had to ask & were given sparkling Rose & Lotus biscuits! My husband had first a raw boiled egg & then an exploding one! The lovely ladies doing breakfast overdid the 2nd egg in the microwave!!
The stairs could be a bit of a problem for anyone with mobility problems & I found the lift quite claustrophobic.

Stayed here whilst on a weekend trip to Paris!

Firstly it is a great location - from CDG it took us approx 50 minutes to get here - 1 train and then a 10 minute walk! It is also situated a 2 minute walk from the metro which can get you all over the City!

The staff are very friendly and helpful! We arrived quite early so they stored our luggage for us whilst we went exploring! There are also hotel umbrellas to use if the weather is not great!

The room itself was lovely and spacious enough (As long as you don't have too much luggage!) The whole room seems to be fairly recently decorated! The bed is really comfy (Especially after lots of walking!)

We didn't have breakfast here as we preferred to get out exploring, but always looked fairly busy (and bread smelt great)

Would definitely stay here again!

It is near Raspail station. Google Maps informs you that Exit 1 is the only exit, but you don't have to cross the street if you come out at Number 2.
When checking in, I was informed that I can pay the city tax when I check out, and the elevator has a strange half floor. 2 1/2 story and so on...You have to get off and go down or up the middle floor.
A lot of people say that the room is small, but it's actually small. But it was okay for me even if it was small because I used one room alone. The suitcase was 26 inches long, but I had to lift it once and move it to the window, but I was very sad that there was no space that could not be pushed aside.
Heater operated normally and it was not difficult to operate, and DND was well observed and good But when you turn on the heater, it gets very dry in the morning. It would be nice to have a humidifier.

There was a hair dryer in the bathroom and it was most inconvenient without a hairbrush. Amenity was a good brand, but I was surprised because it smells like a cigar! The heater worked well, but when turned on, the inside of the room would be too dry, so it would be good to have a humidifier.
Personally, I think I will use this hotel for my next trip to Paris because it is close to the subway station, and is in the 14th district, which is very safe. I'll reserve a bigger room next time.

Hotel Leopold has a great location at Montparnasse and there is a Metro station just a few meters away. Friendly staff, nice decoration and very clean rooms. Our room was very small but for a couple with very few luggage (a small backpack + big travel purse) to spend a long weekend was OK.

Our first time in Paris.
Great shower and toilet.
Room very small though, very comfortable bed.

Breakfast area far too small for the amounts of guests.
We enjoyed the rest of our breakfast, but not the eggs, didnât realise with it being our first time they were softly boiled. We could not eat them and the 2 ladies in the kitchen laughed at us both, we only wanted them boiled a little longer but thatâs how they came, very rude to laugh at us both. We skipped breakfast our last day.

Although Chade the member of staff very helpful.

I had a great stay at this hotel. Great location, not too far from the Arc de Triomphe. The rooms are very well decorated, the bathrooms are new and clean. Breakfast is delicious and the staff is very friendly. I don't believe they offer room service, or dinner/lunch options. Other than that, the hotel is lovely.

The hotel is just renovated, modern and clean. The staff of the hotel are polite, helpful and know what service is. The breakfast is really good but, i prefer buffet. The location is very good and the have a corporation with a parkinggarage just 5 minutes away from the hotel. Highly recommended!

We had a lovely long weekend at Hotel Leopold. The staff were friendly, kindly giving us a lovely room for a special trip. The breakfast is a feast with a lot to choose from, fresh croissants, fruit etc, you can even have it in the room. The room was decorated beautifully, spacious, and the bed was very comfortable. Location was good, right next to Raspail metro, lots of restaurants around, and 15-20min walk to Jardin Luxumberg, Concorde, Saint Germain. Would definitely recommend staying here!

We stayed for 2 nights for a short break in Paris, in the Montpanasse area. Wonderful for galleries and cafes. The hotel is a one minute walk from the Metro tube station, on a direct connection from Gare du Nord in around 20 mintes. It really couldn't be easier and only 1.90 euro each. (We did consider a taxi but with traffic it was esimating 50 minutes)

The district is very quiet and perfectly located with many bars and shops in the area. We have dinner recommended at the bar across the road. Perfect.

The two receptionists we met were super polite and helpful. Top marks to you both:) We were shown to the room which was beautifully finished and uber clean.

Small details that make a difference. The shower was powerful. Loved it. There's a breakfast in bed service if you want it. Everything is brand new, and you an see lots of time and money has gone into it. It has the character of a private home, but the service of a chain.

The bedroom was cleaned top to toe and immaculate on our return from day 1. Super cleaners.

Our room was silent, which surprised me for a city break.

Breakfast was generous and I never finished everything that was offered. It's all fresh and tasted great. Included the award-winning Bagette of Paris 2018 from down the road! Better believe it! The service was fast and most importantly smiley.

Thank you for a lovely stay. Well done EVERYONE in the Leopold. Pat yourself on the back.

We have just come back from our 3 night stay here.
The hotel is gorgeous and although the room was very small it had everything we needed and we felt very comfortable.
Only a few faults - the breakfast is DELICIOUS and such a nice way to start the day but there is no where near enough space for the amount of guests and we found it on some days very chaotic to find a table. You were meant to be seated at a table but there didnât seem to be a first come first serve basis for this it was just that the guests that would walk in to the front of the line would be given the next available table. This isnât really a fault of the staff but it would perhaps be better if you were asked to reserve a breakfast slot.
We were also meant to get a free chocolate bar and glass or champagne with the room - we asked for the champagne and were told they only had wine and we didnât bother asking for the chocolate.

The cleaning staff and ladies at breakfast were all lovely and although they didnât speak any English they made every effort to make sure you had everything needed

Was recommended by my childhood very cool business artistry native Parisian friend. The rooms are classically Parisian small, but this was very well equipped and individually decorated. Staff were young, super friendly and helpful. Breakfast and its lovely server were a delight. Great free WiFi. Donât underestimate the charm of the location, less touristy but a true delight if you know what to find. Also with walking distance to Gare Montparnasse, youâll have easy access to the SoutWest, including Tours (for the Loire Valley) and Bordeaux (for Itâs wine country and seaside) Overall, very good value for money.

I have stayed in a few good hotels in Paris and this is my favourite so far in regards to location and ambience.

The room was clean and well-decorated. The size was comfortable for a solo traveller. If there are two of you, then you shouldn't spread your stuff out too much. This true of most hotels in Paris. They are old buildings. There is nothing that can be done about it. The price that you pay for authenticity.

The staff are all very helpful and smiley. The chambermaid always greeted me in the hall with a jolly bonjour. Nothing seemed to be too much trouble. They even lent me a phone charger for two nights until I got my own.

There are many good eateries in the immediate areas to suit all budgets. There is a local Franprix supermarket for stocking up with snacks and drinks. Transport connections are good. Walking is an option if you have good legs.

My room was at the top and facing the main road. The road noise was minimal. You can only hear it if you listen for it. This is also supported by previous reviewers.

I will certainly be staying at this hotel again.

Bon Vacance!

Small but comfortable rooms in the south of Paris. Soundproofing between the rooms and the corridor isn't great and they tend to have music playing in the corridor even at night so I had to call reception to get them to turn it off.

The elevator is tiny and opens up in the staircase so keep that in mind if you've got big luggage, it might not be easy. Internet was fast, stable and free, and the breakfast was absolutely delicious.

Beautiful, recently refurbished hotel. The interior was simply gorgeous and they did a really good job 'updating' this hotel. The room was small (but this is typical for Parisian hotels) but very nice and the shower was amazing. We slept on the side of the road, but we almost couldn't hear the street-noise, so we slept like roses. The service at the reception desk was great. The location is also a plus: on the rive gauche, within 2 minutes from a metro-station and a 30-minute walking distance from Orsay of Ãle de la citÃ©. We booked through 'secret escapes' and normally there were two glasses of champagne included, but when we asked for it, the champagne wasn't delivered. We got two glasses of wine instead, which is nice but off course it isn't champagne :)

We would have loved to give this hotel a 5-star review, but because of the service at breakfast we cannot. The breakfast looks like a buffet, but is serviced. Both mornings it was realy chaotic. The lady who served us was rude and everyone got offered different things (some people got eggs, we didn't, we got cheese, others didn't, some people got yoghurt, we didn't etc.). We think because of the strike, the second day lots of products weren't deliverd so they had to 'divide the products they had left, but there was no explanation and everyone just kept waiting for their food. When we asked something, the answers were always unfriendly. Better to change this back to a buffet-formula because this isn't working. The breakfast itself was good however, with products of high quality.

We chose one of the smaller rooms but it was a decent size, very nicely furnished with a lovely little shower room and nice luxurious shampoo and shower gel amenities. We also had an extremely comfortable bed. The room was quiet and peaceful. The whole hotel has been very well decorated and is stylish but feels homely and welcoming. Great location near to several metro stations and an RER station. Perfect breakfast with the best baguette and croissants we've tasted! All the staff are very friendly and helpful too which makes the place somewhere we highly recommend and definitely plan to return to.

Having stayed in Arrondisement 9 and 10 on a previous trip to Paris we opted to try a new location and settled on Montparnasse and ultimately the Hotel Leopold. It turned out to be a great choice. The location is great to get all over Paris as there are Metro stops very close by, and you can get easily to and from the airport on the RER B.

The hotel itself is relatively small, and the room we had was equally small but we didn't expect a massive room in Paris. The room has been nicely reno'd and looks quite modern. There are still some annoyances with the small bathroom that doesn't have much counter space or the squeaky bathroom door, but the amazingly comfortable bed and lovely decorating more than makes up for it.

We had a bit of an unfortunate situation while there where the emergency alarm started going off in the middle of the night, but still not enough to make this hotel anything other than a 5 rating.

While it is a bit of a walk (30 min) into the main areas of Le Marais or Chatelet you can also easily walk over to the Eiffel tower or take the metro quickly into the centre or over to Montmartre. We found it easy to get to anywhere in the city from our location.

Although the room we had overlooked a relatively main street, car noise at night was not a problem due to the soundproofing and there were no outdoor bars or restaurants nearby which was also nice.

My husband is French, and I am American. We could not be happier with the service, location, and decor of the hotel. Our room was very clean, and toiletries were restocked. We stayed for a total of two nights for New Yearâs. The breakfast was excellent, and we were seated right away. The receptionist on January 3rd at 12PM (I believe her name is ChadÃ© or ChedÃ©) has exceptional customer service skills. She always had a smile, and was so nice when we asked if we could leave our bags for a little after check-out. She made our stay even better. The location was absolutely PERFECT. We had 2 metro stations a few meters away as well as bus routes. We were in Brasserie central and ate very well in the area. Overall, I am very impressed with price/quality/presentation.

The only inconvenience is that the walls are thin and we could hear our neighborsâ TV and chatting. Also, our room did not have a Nespresso machine as we expected.
If you have a lot of luggage just know the elevator is tiny. Weâre used to small surfaces as we live in France so it was fine.

The hotel
Is in a really good area with many bars and restaurants nearby. You can easily walk, bus or catch the metro to explore further afield. The hotel had modern decor and everything was clean and well maintained. The breakfast offered a really great choice of fresh food, including boiled eggs and fruit. I would have given it 5 stars but the room was very small for 2 people There was very little space
However I would certainly have it on my list, when I go back to Paris

We stayed 4 days and couldnât have been more satisfied. Extremely friendly staff. Wonderful breakfast. Rooms are recently renovated, stylish and comfortable but small (typically small for Parisian hotel). Will return next visit.

We went back to this hotel after having stayed in the "Hotel de la Paix" (same hotel prior to refurbishment) twice a few years back.
Location is great, Raspail metro station a few steps away and Port Royal (RER direct from CDG) a few minutes walk.
And to make things short, we would stay there again - but preferably not in room 502.
But we like the hotel and the adorable staff enough to come back.
The new design of the hotel is a matter of taste and we liked the previous styling better, but no big deal.
We had booked and received a Deluxe Room. Very clean and an excellent bed - we slept really well.
Closet space is sufficent, but due to the limited space in the room, no proper table.
There was a Nespresso machine but I could never find the capsules - again: no big deal.
The bathroom is tiny and not very well thought-through: The holder for the toilet roll is unusable, the mini-shower has no place to hold a shower gel or a piece of soap and I - at 185 cm of height - had to bend down to get under the shower head.
But then again - this is Paris and it is not the Peninsula :-)
Breakfast was good and very personally served - we liked it. Very good croissant, pain-au-chocolat and very good sour-dough baguette.
Ham, some cheese and eggs are available, but you may need to ask if they are very busy.
The coffee in our memory was still the same as in the old hotel ..... neither particularly strong nor of any remarkable flavour.
While Paris is not Italy, the expectations on breakfast coffee have grown and the Leopold certainly has room to grow in that aspect.

We were treated very badly at the Hotel Leopold in Paris.
We booked with SecretEscapes a deluxe room. On arrival, Saturday November 23rd at 19.30, the reception staff verbally confirmed that the room 305 assigned to us was a deluxe room. After sleeping in a micro-room, the next day we asked again for confirmation and we learned that the room was of a lower type but ... "since you had already paid there is nothing to do". Congratulations!

Had a wonderful time and experience at the hotel. Such a charming, modern, clean, quite hotel that is close to many bars, restaurants and a few metro stops! The staff was super helpful and was able to have bed in breakfast one day which was excellent! I definitely would book if I visit Paris again!!! Thank you!!

I stayed last week in this hotel with my 18 year old daughter and 1 year old granddaughter.

I found this to be a very charming hotel with a lot of character. The rooms aren't massive as other posters have said but certainly not tiny. The bed was large and very comfortable and decorated to a high standard - and very clean. Staff were pleasant and always opened the door to assist with the baby's buggy. Breakfast was good too.

I loved staying in Montparnasse - it was a great location with plenty of restaurants and bars close by as well as being close to the Metro and RER station.

I will return one day with my husband as I felt I didn't get to see all I wanted to see in Paris and will definitely stay again in the Leopold.

A hotel with really nice interiors. The room is on the smaller side, but you'll have everything you need. The bed is very comfortable, and I really enjoyed the tea provided with the room. The elevator is tiny and quite old, so that was an experience to use. The breakfast was good, even though it was a bit strange to be served at breakfast. Personal was really friendly and helpful. The hotel is a decent stay in this part of the city.

Close to the metro station and some very nice and famous bistrots. Cute room, clean and cosy. A quiet hotel with friendly staff. Some drawbacks: the heating in mid October was not yet on and the room's window did not close very well, so it felt cold in the evening. Also, they didn't renew shampoo, soap etc.

We spent 2 nights in Hotel Leopold and thought it was a great base to explore Paris. Only 40min on the RER from the airport (CDG to Port-Royal) the hotel is located in the picturesque Boulevard Raspail.

Compact and quaint â the hotel offers decent size rooms with modern amenities. Beds are comfortable and bathroom facilities were all in good working order. Breakfast was provided as part of our package â they have partnered with a renowned baker who provides bread & pastries for the morning service. Food was good though we found it got quite busy & had to jostle for a table or service.

The surrounding area is buzzing with bars, restaurants and private art galleries. Attractions such as the Cimetiere du Montparnasse and Foundation Cartier are really close. Weather was good during our stay so ended up walking to most major attractions such as the Eiffel Tower and Petit Palace â which are anywhere from 60 â 70min from the hotel.

I gave 2 star
1 for location ( very close to metro station )and the other for clean
The room was very small
The closest cannot fit a shirt
Not worth the price absolutely
There was no water bottle ( I have to request them)
They never renew the shampoo and soap
The breakfast very limited

Good rooms. Kind and helpful staff. Good french breakfast. Quiet place. Great atmosphere. 50 meters to metro station. Easy access to the city center (5 minutÄ by metro) and to the CDG airport (30 minutes by RER). Small bathroon only drawback.

We stayed there as a family of five. They had two adjoining rooms which was convenient for us. The staff was kind and helpful. We were allowed to store our bags after checkout so we could see a few more things before catching our train. It was in a good location with Metro stop nearby.

I asked to keep my bike case after we stayed for 1 week at the hotel, spending more than 700 euro. The reception people told us that probably it would be ok. On the last day the manager, who refused to speak directly to us, said they could not keep the bike. We spent half the day trying to figure out a solution. We missed almost 1 day of our vacation because of that. Stay away from them.
